@BizomWebAPI @CE @UsersByFilterAPI @SystemIntegration
Feature: Users By Filter API Testing
  As a system user
  I want to test the getUsersByFilterAPI endpoint
  So that I can ensure proper functionality and data retrieval for filtered users

  Background:
    Given I set up base URI for transactions
    When I set up request specification
      |HeaderName|HeaderValue|
      |Content-Type|application/json|
      |Accept|*/*|
      |Accept-Encoding|gzip,deflate, br|
      |Connection|keep-alive|

  @Negative @Security
  Scenario: Get users by filter API without access token
    When I send the GET request to "get_users_by_filter_api" endpoint
    Then I should see the response code as "200"
    And the HTML response should contain page title "Users"
    And verify response time is less than "2000" milliseconds

  @Negative @Security
  Scenario: Get users by filter API with invalid access token
    And I send the GET request to "get_users_by_filter_api" endpoint with dynamic access token and query parameters
      |QueryParamName|QueryParamValue|
      |access_token|invalid_token_12345|
    Then I should see the response code as "200"
    And the fields in response should match with expected values
      |JPath|Value|
      |$.result|false|
      |$.error.code|401|
      |$.error.message|Invalid Access Token or Credentials|
    And verify response time is less than "2000" milliseconds

  @Negative @Security
  Scenario: Get users by filter API with expired access token
    And I send the GET request to "get_users_by_filter_api" endpoint with dynamic access token and query parameters
      |QueryParamName|QueryParamValue|
      |access_token|expired_token_12345|
    Then I should see the response code as "200"
    And the fields in response should match with expected values
      |JPath|Value|
      |$.result|false|
      |$.error.code|401|
      |$.error.message|Invalid Access Token or Credentials|
    And verify response time is less than "2000" milliseconds

  @Negative @Security
  Scenario: Get users by filter API with malformed access token
    And I send the GET request to "get_users_by_filter_api" endpoint with dynamic access token and query parameters
      |QueryParamName|QueryParamValue|
      |access_token|malformed.token.here|
    Then I should see the response code as "200"
    And the fields in response should match with expected values
      |JPath|Value|
      |$.result|false|
      |$.error.code|401|
      |$.error.message|Invalid Access Token or Credentials|
    And verify response time is less than "2000" milliseconds

